The Booker Prize has become internationally known, and winning the prize is a boon to 
the author and publisher. The 1990 winner will be announced on 16 October, and a 
worldwide boost of sales of the winning novel will follow.

Each British publishing house can submit for consideration up to three novels by British 
or Commonwealth authors. A management committee selects a well-qualified panel of 
judges who meet and select the six finalists. Interest builds and bookmakers establish 
odds on each author's chance of winning. The judges announce the winner in the 
afternoon of announcement day.</SUM>

<SUM
