Yesterday' announcement of the short-list of six contenders for the1994 Booker Prize 
elicited some biting comments. Some of those on the list were characterized as "B-Team 
Writers at the Best". This is surprising in a year of good works of fiction that meet the 
criteria for Booker consideration in that they are written in English and are non-
American. They are missing from the short-list, making the criticism more strident.

Despite the carping, there will be the usual high interest from now until 11 October when 
the winner is announced.</SUM>

<SUM
