SUMMARIZER="C">

The winner of the Booker Prize for 1944 will be announced on 11 October. Five days 
later the winner of the hypothetical 1894 booker Prize will be named at the Cheltenham 
Festival of Literature. It is a publishing gimmick, but it is also a fascinating exercise in 
historical reconstruction.

The short-list is a sensation. It includes such classics as Kilpling's "Jungle Book", George 
du Maurier's "Trilby", and Anthony Hope's "The Prisoner of Zenda". All the 1894 
Booker writers were popular names but also serious skillful writers whose books can be 
read with pleasure 100 years later.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d117"
TYPE="PERDOC"
